The defendant Crystal A Norby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Crystal A Norby in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 450.11(7)(h), a class U Misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

Court sentenced defendant to serve ONE (1) DAY in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for ONE (1) days served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, by 08-29-2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Filed,

Signature bond remains at $500.00 in this matter. Court modifies conditions and orders defendant released to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY to be monitored by drug testing and portable breathalyzers.  No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription, no drug paraphernalia and no alcohol. Defendant to notify Justice Point agent of all prescriptions within 72 hours of receiving prescription from any Doctor.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings. Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping. Defendant advised to report to Justice Point after court.
